is confined and not observed as a scattering state.  In the case of                       
two-body  states, the antitriplets are diquarks which, inside a                       
hadron can be combined with another triplet quark to give                       
observable, color singlet, three-quark baryon states.  The color                       
sextet part of  can only combine with a third quark to give                       
unobservable color octet and color decuplet three-quark states.                        
