Chiral Lagrangians with Vector Mesons 

In the large  expansion baryons emerge as solitons within an effective theory of infinitely many weakly interacting mesons. A more realistic model should include not just the pseudoscalar meson field but also other heavier vector mesons. If we assume the 's, 's and 's form an  multiplet, they should be treated in a unified manner. Accordingly, we now consider an  matrix configuration of these mesons

 
