Vector Mesons as Gauge Bosons 
Gauge potentials can be obtained from the decomposition of a larger algebra into a subalgebra and a coset. Gauge bosons can be combined with the fundamental mesons to form a single multiplet so that all mesons are treated equally in the larger symmetry group. 

We can write  in terms of the new variables  and  

 
